<Issue id="20227" key="FAB-5808" number="5808" project="10002" reporter="jyellick" assignee="jyellick" creator="jyellick" type="10003" summary="Add configtx.Manager reference to immutable config" priority="3" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2017-08-17 04:46:44.0" updated="2018-07-20 14:14:07.0" resolutiondate="2017-09-03 13:58:31.0" votes="0" watches="1" workflowId="39764"> <description><! CDATA The immutable bundle does not need the configtx manager to actually parse the config or policies, but it does need a way authorize new configurations.  Therefore, the channel config needs to be fed to the configtx.Manager, but without injecting a new dependency onto the mutable logic.  This CR introduces a noop value and policy proposer so that the configtx.Manager code can continue to authorize configuration updates without injecting this new mutability dependency.  Once there are no more dependencies on the configtx value/policy proposals, this noop implementation will be deleted.  ></description> </Issue>
